com.paydiant.android.ui.service.mobilecash

Class ATMCashServiceListenerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.ui.service.mobilecash.ATMCashServiceListenerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IATMCashServiceListener

    public class ATMCashServiceListenerAdapter
extends Object
implements IATMCashServiceListener
    This class provides an empty implementation for IATMCashServiceListener. Any classes that wants to use only a subset of the listener methods can override the relevant methods and use it as the interface implementation. 

     ATMCashServiceListenerAdapter atmCashServiceListenerAdapter = new ATMCashServiceListenerAdapter() {
 
    @Override
    public void onSubmitATMCashAmountSuccess(CashTransactionResult cashTransactionResult) {
    }
 
    @Override
    public void onATMCashServiceError(PaydiantException exception) {
    }
 };
 iatmCashService.setATMCashServiceListener(atmCashServiceListenerAdapter);
    Note: App developers are encouraged to use the ListenerAdapter implementations whenever possible as the Listener interfaces might get updated with new functionality/methods from one SDK release to the other. Therefore using a ListenerAdapter will make sure that there wont be any compilation issues due to unimplemented methods during a SDK upgrade.
